Introduce R6 compatible stubbing
body:
This pull request addresses the issue raised in https://github.com/n-s-f/mockery/issues/13.

In addition, it introduces the ability to stub out namespaced functions, e.g.

```R
stub(httr::GET, 'request_perform', 'some response')
```

Finally, it removes code that confirms method calls. That functionality has been taken over by mock objects.

title: Add mock obj
body:
Hey Noam,

Here's the pull request. One thing I've noticed is that your expect_called does not follow testthat's flow of executing expectations after running the code under test - your expect_called needs to be write before the code under test is run. I think this can turn out to be confusing if people use this package with testthat.

Lukasz
